article.headline: Hawaii 83, Fresno St. 66
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Six Rainbow Warriors scored in double figures to lead Hawaii to an 83-66 victory over Fresno State on Thursday night. Dominic Waters led Hawaii (10-6, 1-2 Western Athletic Conference) with 15 points. Bobby Nash added 14 points, Matt Lojeski 13, P.J. Owsley 12, Riley Luettgerodt 11 and Ahmet Gueye 10 for the Rainbow Warriors. It was the first time six Hawaii players scored in double figures since 2002. Eddie Miller led Fresno State (13-3, 2-1 WAC) with 13 points. Kevin Bell and Quinton Hosley added 12 points each for the Bulldogs. After leading 44-24 at halftime, Hawaii outscored Fresno State 17-8 in the first five minutes of the second half to extend its lead to 29 points, 61-32. A late 11-2 run by Fresno State pulled the Bulldogs to within 17, 83-66, the closest margin since two minutes remaining in the first half. The Rainbow Warriors used a three-minute, 12-0 run to go up by 23 points, 44-21, with 38 seconds remaining in the first half. Hawaii shot 56 percent from the field in the first half to 30 percent for Fresno State, which missed its first 10 shots of the game.
